  "hostile-attitude": "Hostile Attitude:",
  "friendly-attitude-description": "The creature or person seeks closeness and contact with the characters. They try to invite them into their life and give all they can, even at great personal cost. The feeling may prove much stronger, bordering on love or a willingness to sacrifice themselves for the characters.",
  "helpful-attitude-description": "The creature or person approaches the characters with sympathy and trust. They clearly try to be helpful, even if it costs them time, effort, or resources. They also try to leave a clear impression that the characters can count on them in the future.",
  "positive-attitude-description": "The creature or person is clearly interested in the characters and what they want. If they can help without obvious cost to themselves, they will gladly cooperate.",
  "neutral-attitude-description": "The creature or person is neutral. Their behavior depends on the characters' attitude, conduct, and demands. If they feel they can be properly rewarded for their help, they will cooperate according to the characters' expectations.",
  "suspicious-attitude-description": "The creature or person keeps their distance and would rather end the interaction as quickly as possible. Their attitude favors short, blunt answers, and they will not go out of their way to help the characters.",
  "reluctant-attitude-description": "The creature or person treats the characters with clear reserve and shows it in their posture. They clearly do not want contact, and if pressured they may become aggressive. They will act against the encountered characters even without any obvious benefit.",
  "hostile-attitude-description": "The creature or person is aggressive. If they feel they have the advantage, they will attack. Otherwise, they will try to intimidate through their behavior and by displaying weapons. If cornered, they will defend themselves. No agreement is possible; the creature or person will gladly harm the characters.",
